{"lemma":"أَتْرِبَةُ","slug":"أَتْرِبَةُ","root":"ت.ر.ب","root_slug":"ت-ر-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ت-ر-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"تُراب","root":"ترب","pos":"N","occurrence_count":17},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n3837"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%AA%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%90%D8%A8%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"earth, soil, ground, dust (organic material, sand, etc., which covers the land)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"land, territory, soil","tags":["figuratively"],"examples":[{"text":"أَرادَت أَن تَرْجِعَ إلَى تُرابِ الوَطَن.","english":"She wanted to return to the homeland’s soil."}]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/tu.raːb/","/traːb/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n3837","headword_ar":"تُرَابٌ","root":"trb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"turobN","text_ar":"تُرْبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, T, S, M, A, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tarobN","text_ar":"تَرْبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(CK [but this I do not find elsewhere]) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"turobapF","text_ar":"تُرْبَةً","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, * K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tarobaA='u","text_ar":"تَرْبَا=ءُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, T, S, A, * K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"turabaA='u","text_ar":"تُرَبَا=ءُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taworaAbN","text_ar":"تَوْرَابٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taworabN","text_ar":"تَوْرَبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tayoraAbN","text_ar":"تَيْرَابٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tayorabN","text_ar":"تَيْرَبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tayrabN","text_ar":"تَيرَبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"as will be seen below] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tariybN","text_ar":"تَرِيبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tiroyabN","text_ar":"تِرْيَبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K) accord. to MF ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taroyabN","text_ar":"تَرْيَبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is perhaps a dial. var., and accord. to some ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tiroyibN","text_ar":"تِرْيِبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taroyaAbN","text_ar":"تَرْيَابٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) signify the same, (Lth, T, S, M, A, K,) and are words of which the meaning is well known: (A, K:) [i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Dust:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"earth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"generally the former; i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fine, dry, particles of earth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as when we say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~iyHu tasuwqu Alt~uraAba","text_ar":"الرِّيحُ تَسُوقُ التُّرَابَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The wind drives along the dust:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but we also use the expression"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"turaAbN nadK","text_ar":"تُرَابٌ نَدٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"moist earth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"the explanation, in Lexicons, of the word"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"varFY","text_ar":"ثَرًى"},{"kind":"text","text":":]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"?varFY","text_ar":"?ثَرًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"turaAbN","text_ar":"تُرَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and when it ceases to be moist, it is still"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"trAb","text_ar":"تراب"},{"kind":"text","text":", but is not then called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vrY","text_ar":"ثرى"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vrY","text_ar":"ثرى"},{"kind":"text","text":":) accord. to Fr,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"turaAbN","text_ar":"تُرَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a gen. n., from which is formed neither dual nor pl.: and its rel. n. is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"turaAbiY~N","text_ar":"تُرَابِىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) [but when it means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a kind of dust"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"earth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"turobapN","text_ar":"تُرْبَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"also does sometimes, it has a pl.: in this case,] accord. to Lh, (M,) its pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^atoribapN","text_ar":"اَتْرِبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a pl. of pauc.] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tirobaAnN","text_ar":"تِرْبَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[a pl. of mult.]; (S, M, K) and some add"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"turobaAnN","text_ar":"تُرْبَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) [and when ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"turobapN","text_ar":"تُرْبَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"has this, or a similar, meaning, it has for its pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"turabN","text_ar":"تُرَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; as in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aToyabu Alt~urabi","text_ar":"اَطْيَبُ التُّرَبِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the best of the kinds of earth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"occurring in this art. in the A:] but no pl. of any of the other syn. words mentioned above has been heard: (M, K:) AAF says that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"trAb","text_ar":"تراب"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"trb","text_ar":"ترب"},{"kind":"text","text":"; [app. meaning that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"turaAbN","text_ar":"تُرَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a quasi-pl. n. (which is often called in lexicons a pl.) of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"turobN","text_ar":"تُرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";] but MF observes that this requires consideration: (TA:) Lth says that ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"turobN","text_ar":"تُرْبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"turaAbN","text_ar":"تُرَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"are syn.; but when the fem. forms of these words are used, they say, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroDN Tay~bapu Alt~urobap","text_ar":"اَرْضٌ طَيّبَةُ التُّرْبَة","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Land that is good in respect of the natural constitution of its dust"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"earth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"turaAbapN","text_ar":"تُرَابَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"when meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A layer,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lamina, of dust"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"earth, such as is not perceived by the sight, but only by the imagination:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T:) or this last word and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"turobapN","text_ar":"تُرْبَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a portion of dust"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"earth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aroDi","text_ar":"الاَرْضِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"turobapu","text_ar":"تُرْبَةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the exterior,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"external part, of the earth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~arobaA='u","text_ar":"التَّرْبَا=ءُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the earth"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"itself."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) The Arabs said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~uraAbu laka","text_ar":"التُّرَابُ لَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Dust,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"earth, be thy lot"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; using the nom. case, although meaning an imprecation, because the word is a simple subst., not an inf. n.: but Lh mentions the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~uraAba liloA^aboEadi","text_ar":"التُّرَابَ لِلْاَبْعَدِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Dust,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"earth, be the lot of the remote from good"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; saying that the accus. case is used, as though the phrase were an imprecation [of the ordinary kind, in which an inf. n. is used in the accus. case as the absolute complement of its own verb understood]. (M.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lahu Alt~uraAbu","text_ar":"لَهُ التُّرَابُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a phrase used as meaning (assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He has,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shall have,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"may he have,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disappointment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ehr","text_ar":"عهر"},{"kind":"text","text":",) or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nothing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A 'Obeyd, Mgh in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fr$","text_ar":"فرش"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lahu wajanodalFA","text_ar":"لَهُ وَجَنْدَلًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"turobFA","text_ar":"تُرْبًا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also a form of imprecation, in which substs. in the proper sense of the term are used in the manner of inf. ns., put in the accus. case by reason of a verb unexpressed; as though it were for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taribato yadaAhu wajunodilato","text_ar":"تَرِبَتْ يَدَاهُ وَجُنْدِلَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"May his arms,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his hands, cleave to the dust,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"earth, and the stones,"},{"kind":"text","text":"by reason of poverty]: and some of the Arabs put the nouns in the nom. case, still using the phrase in the same sense, as though they were in the accus. (M.) One says also, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bifiyhi Alt~aworabu","text_ar":"بِفِيهِ التَّوْرَبُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~ayorabu","text_ar":"التَّيْرَبُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~iyirabu","text_ar":"التِّيِرَبُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~arobaA='u","text_ar":"التَّرْبَا=ءُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~aworaAbu","text_ar":"التَّوْرَابُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In his mouth is dust,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"earth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"may dust,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"earth, be in his mouth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. may he die, or be in his grave]. (T.) It is said in a trad. that God created the ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"turobap","text_ar":"تُرْبَة","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dust,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soil,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, accord. to the TA the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"earth"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroD","text_ar":"اَرْض"},{"kind":"text","text":"),] on the seventh day of the week; and created upon it the mountains on the first day; and the trees, on the second day. (T.) And one says, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA^aDoriban~ahu Hat~aY yaEaD~a biAlt~arobaA='i","text_ar":"لَاَضْرِبَنَّهُ حَتَّى يَعَضَّ بِالتَّرْبَا=ءِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lth, T, A,) meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I will assuredly beat him so that he shall bite"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the dust,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"earth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, T.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayonahumaA maA bayona AljarobaA='i waAlt~arobaA='i","text_ar":"بَيْنَهُمَا مَا بَيْنَ الجَرْبَا=ءِ وَالتَّرْبَا=ءِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Between them two is the space that is between"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the heaven and the earth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.)"}],"source_refs":["Lth","T","S","M","A","Msb","K","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}